<problem name="Flags">
    <description>
		<p>On the Day of the Flag of Russia a shop-owner decided to decorate the show-window of his shop with textile stripes of white, blue and red colors. He wants to satisfy the following conditions:</p>
		<ol>
			<li>Stripes of the same color cannot be placed next to each other.</li>
			<li>A blue stripe must always be placed between a white and a red or between a red and a white one.</li>
		</ol>
		<p>Determine the number of the ways to fulfill his wish.</p>
		<p><b>Example.</b> For <tt>N = 3</tt> result is following:</p>
		<img pos="center" src="images/flags.png" />
		<h2>Input specifications</h2>
		<p><tt>N</tt>, the number of the stripes, <tt>1 &leq; N &leq; 45</tt>.</p>
		<h2>Output specifications</h2>
		<p><tt>M</tt>, the number of the ways to decorate the shop-window.</p>
    </description>
    <solution include="solution.cpp" language="C++" />
    <tests timelimit="3s" memorylimit="64MB">
        <test example="true">
            <input><![CDATA[3]]></input>
            <output><![CDATA[4]]></output>
        </test>
        <test input_include="tests/T0.in" output_include="tests/T0.out" />
        <test input_include="tests/T1.in" output_include="tests/T1.out" />
